      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "VINNIE NITRO (2) has recorded two wins and three minor placings from the past five starts. Didn't let supporters down at her latest appearance when she got the job done by a head over 1780m at this track. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Meets a comparable field so she can keep the ball rolling. ULTIMATE ARK (9) drew wide last start and was never a genuine threat, beaten 11 metres into seventh at Albion Park over 1660m. This easier and rates a leading hope if he is at his best. LITTLE SURFER GIRL (3) disappointed last time when seventh over 1780m here. Can turn things around from the low draw. ZAC DANIELS (5) has put the writing on the wall with a couple of seconds recently, the latest at this circuit over 2040m. One for the multiples.",
